          <!-- Author and Date -->
          <div class="author scale-12 padded margin-24-tb clearfix">
              <div class="ideas-author-inner">
              <div class="ideas-indicator">Ideas</div>
            <div class="author-text" data-tracking-zone="author">
                <div class="padding-8-right">
                    By 
                      <a class="bold author-name" href="/author/robert-redford/">
                        Robert Redford
                      </a>
                </div>
                      <div class="timestamp published-date padding-12-left">
                    April 22, 2019
                  </div>
                  <div class="author-bio"><em>Redford is an actor, a director, a trustee of the Natural Resources Defense Council and co-founder of The Redford Center. </em></div>
                </div>
            </div>
          </div>


        <!-- Article Content -->
        <div id="article-body" class="article content body clearfix" data-tracking-zone="body">
          <div class="padded">
                <p><span class="dropcap">C</span>ollusion, <a href="https://time.com/5573521/donald-trump-obstruction-justice/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">obstruction of justice</a>, impeachment or not, greedy tax breaks, medical care for all or none, refugees seeking compassion at our borders &mdash; as a citizen, I care deeply about all these things. But I also fail to see how any of it will matter <a href="https://time.com/5550823/climate-change-protest-schoolchildren/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">without a planet</a> to live on.</p>
                <p>We are approaching an <a href="https://time.com/5418134/ipcc-climate-change-report-2030-crisis/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">irreversible tipping point</a>. The science of climate change is backed by examples of the damage mankind has caused all around us, every day and everywhere. None of us are immune anymore; no matter where we live, <a href="https://time.com/5462102/climate-change-report-trump-science/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">no matter our political party</a>.</p>
                <p>I can&rsquo;t think of anything that should compel and demand our attention more. What will it take for our <a href="https://time.com/5554996/epa-chief-climate-change-threat/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">short-sighted leadership</a> to stop questioning the reality of this global crisis?</p>
                <p>It&rsquo;s hard to believe, but 49 years ago a new awareness of our environmental responsibilities was born. The <a href="https://time.com/3772160/earth-day/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">founding of Earth Day</a> marked an important moment in time, a pivotal recognition of how precious and fragile and sacred our connection is to our natural world. And on this Earth Day, I find myself searching for words to express my <a href="https://time.com/5530374/europe-climate-change/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sense of urgency</a> on behalf of our one and only home &mdash; to create yet another new awareness of those same responsibilities.</p>
                
                
                  <div
                     id="ad-300x250_320x480_LL_m_1" 
                    data-tgxtrack="true" data-tgxtargeting="%7B%7D" data-tgxupdatecorrelator="true" data-tgxlazy="200"
                    class="ad ad-container ad-wrapper type-300x250;320x480 instream-ad mobile-ad"
                    data-dimensions="300x250;320x480" role="complementary" aria-hidden="true">
                  </div>
                
                
                  <div
                     id="ad-728x90_LL_td_1" 
                    data-tgxtargeting="%7B%7D" data-tgxlazy="200"
                    class="ad ad-container ad-wrapper type-728x90 instream-ad tablet-ad desktop-ad x2"
                    data-dimensions="728x90" role="complementary" aria-hidden="true">
                  </div>
                <p>President Trump has promised to withdraw from the <a href="https://time.com/5195459/climate-change-trump-paris-agreement-patricia-espinosa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Paris Agreement</a>, appointed climate change deniers to <a href="https://time.com/5569214/epa-chief-andrew-wheeler-climate-change/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">head the EPA</a>, weakened protections for clean air and water, and tried to cut funding efforts to advance renewable energy. He has made terrible decisions followed by worse decisions.</p>
                <p>It&rsquo;s heartbreaking, yet we&rsquo;re all in this mess together.</p>
                <p>It&rsquo;d be pretty thoughtless to pretend we&rsquo;re not <a href="https://time.com/5433987/guns-common-ground/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">divided right now in America</a>. There are many complex reasons for this, but I stubbornly continue to believe that more unites us underneath it all, and that when push comes to shove, we all want a better and <a href="https://time.com/5547063/hans-blix-nuclear-energy-environment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">healthier future</a> for our children and grandchildren.</p>
                
                <div class="component video margin-32-bottom ">
                    <div class="jumpstart-video">
                      <video 
                      id="video-6014082801001"
                      class="video-js vjs-fluid"
                      data-embed="default"
                      data-controls="true"
                      controls=""
                      data-account="293884104"
                      data-player="gh5LeNtQaQ"
                      data-video-id="6014082801001"
                      data-autoplay="false"
                      data-continuous-play="true"
                      data-continuous-play="true"
                      data-is-lead="false"></video>
                    </div>
                
                  <div 
                  class="vjs-playlist" 
                  data-for="video-6014082801001" 
                  data-player="gh5LeNtQaQ"
                  data-embed="default"
                  ></div>
                </div>
                <p>Many young people have not waited to ask for permission to change things because, unlike some of us, they&rsquo;ve wisely realized they are literally <a href="https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2019/5567758/greta-thunberg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">fighting for their lives</a>. They&rsquo;ve watched as our leaders unravel protections instead of strengthening them, <a href="https://time.com/5543102/2020-election-climate-change/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">argue endlessly</a> without doing enough to advance innovation, and pass the buck, hoping someone else will save us.</p>
                <div class="component feed inline-recirc double" data-partial="tile" data-variation="inline-recirc double" data-type="feed" data-title="Related Stories" >
                  <h2 class="subtitle feed-subtitle">Related Stories</h2>
                
